column50:
This parameter is specified as duration in the core.yaml file, i.e. "3600s", but is retrieved as if it is a float. (see deliveryclient.go L42)
{code:java}
func getReConnectBackoffThreshold() float64 {
	return util.GetFloat64OrDefault("peer.deliveryclient.reConnectBackoffThreshold", defaultReConnectBackoffThreshold)
}
{code}
As a result, the default is always in effect in the deliveryservice.broadcastClient , no matter what is in the core.yaml file.

The solution is simple: change getReConnectBackoffThreshold() to first get the value as a time.Duration, and then convert it to a float.

